The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 9: Power company AES has signed an MoU with PTC India to sell 800mw power from its coal-based thermal power project, which is being set up in Chhattisgarh. The 1,200mw plant is expected to be commissioned by 2011-12 and the capacity from the plant is proposed to be sold through competitive bidding or on merchant basis, the company said.

 New Delhi, July 9: A dozen private sector firms, including Indiabulls, Alok Industries, Alps Industries and Nitco Tiles, have shown interest in partnering the National Textiles Corporation (NTC) to modernise its 16 mills.

 Mumbai, July 9: Dishman Pharmaceuticals amp; Chemicals will acquire the Netherlands-based Solvay Pharmaceuticals fine chemicals, vitamin D and analogues business for an undisclosed amount. The transfer of ownership will be completed this year.

 New Delhi, July 9: The World Banks private sector arm, IFC, will invest Rs 300 crore in Max Healthcare over the next four years through purchase of equity and preference shares to fund the companys capacity expansion.

 Mumbai, July 9: Ashok Leyland has allotted 49.98 lakh shares of Re 1 each upon conversion of foreign currency convertible notes, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.




